<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF99EF59FF42F826FDEAF8D8" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF99EF5AFF42F826FC7DF84D" blockId="49.[151,1436,1867,2038]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF99EF5AFF42F826FEE7F815" bold="true" box="[199,338,1939,1965]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Comments:</emphasis>
The species presents a broad geographic distribution, even if a discontinuity of the records, as the species is absent in most of the Amazon, besides Pantanal and Cerrado, exist. In the same way as for other species of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF99EF5AFF30F86EFEFEF84D" authorityName="Krauss" authorityYear="1902" box="[181,331,2011,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tettigoniidae</taxonomicName>
, such discontinuity is probably due to sampling absence.
</paragraph>
<caption id="09BB5CE3FF9AEF59FF12FA6AFB54F987" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550119" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6550119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550119/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" startId="50.[151,250,1503,1527]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1479]" targetPageId="50">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9AEF59FF12FA6AFB54F987" blockId="50.[151,1437,1503,1599]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF12FA6AFE94FA4F" bold="true" box="[151,289,1503,1527]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">FIGURE 25.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FE1DFA6AFDA9FA4F" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[408,540,1503,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Steirodontini">Steirodontini</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FDACFA6AFD64FA4F" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[553,721,1503,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FC71FA6AFAA6FA4F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1012,1299,1503,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Cnemidophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrifolium">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FC71FA6AFAA6FA4F" box="[1012,1299,1503,1527]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Cnemidophyllum citrifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male; B and C: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FF3DF9B6FE10F9A3" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1970" box="[184,421,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Steirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentiferoides">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF3DF9B6FE10F9A3" box="[184,421,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Steirodon dentiferoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female, respectively; D and E: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FCE4F9B6FC5EF9A3" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1869" box="[865,1003,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Steirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentiferum">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FCE4F9B6FC5EF9A3" box="[865,1003,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">S. dentiferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female, respectively; F and G: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FF12F992FE10F987" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1970" box="[151,421,1575,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Stilpnochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginoides">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF12F992FE10F987" box="[151,421,1575,1599]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Stilpnochlora marginoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female, respectively; H and I: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9AEF59FCC2F992FC2AF987" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1970" box="[839,927,1575,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Stilpnochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanna">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FCC2F992FC2AF987" box="[839,927,1575,1599]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">S. nanna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9AEF59FF42F9D8FC89F977" blockId="50.[151,1436,1645,1888]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF42F9D8FEEEF93F" bold="true" box="[199,347,1645,1671]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF9AEF59FEEFF9D8FE41F930" box="[362,500,1645,1672]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,191,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@51.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 26. Calling songs of species of Steirodontini and of Enthephippion olivaceum. A–C: Cnemidophyllum citrifolium; D–F: Steirodon dentiferoides; G–I: S. dentiferum. A: sonogram of one echeme; B, E and H: sonogram of one syllable; D and G: sonogram of two isolated syllables; C, F and H: spectrogram of the respective syllable." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550123" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550123/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 26A–C</figureCitation>
): Males stridulate only at night. A single echeme, composed by only three syllables, in a crescendo of intensity, is produced. The syllables are composed by several pulses, more spaced in the first two thirds of the syllable, and almost juxtaposed in the last third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9AEF59FF42F96FFDE1F94B" blockId="50.[151,1436,1645,1888]" box="[199,596,1753,1780]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF42F96FFE1EF94B" box="[199,427,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 16 ± 0.8 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9AEF59FF42F948FE45F8AF" blockId="50.[151,1436,1645,1888]" box="[199,496,1789,1816]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF42F948FEF5F8AF" box="[199,320,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 7.7 ± 2.7 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9AEF59FF42F897FC9EF884" blockId="50.[151,1436,1645,1888]" box="[199,811,1825,1852]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9AEF59FF42F897FE9BF883" box="[199,302,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Duration</emphasis>
